OL,5, The government has written off #8.7bn  
OL,6, it spent on protective equipment bought
OL,7, during the pandemic, accounts show.    
OL,9,FThe Department for Health and Social   
OL,10,FCare documents show items costing #673m
OL,11,Fwere unusable, while #750m of equipment
OL,12,Fwas not used before its expiry date.   
OL,14,FThe largest write-off - #4.7bn - was   
OL,15,Fbecause the government paid more for it
OL,16,Fthan it is currently worth, now that   
OL,17,Fglobal supplies have recovered.        
OL,19,FNo 10 said the purchases were justified
OL,20,F- with 97% of items suitable for use.  
